{
  "texts": [
    "The predicted probabilities for the positive and negative classes are influenced by prevalence.",
    "However, the fact that AUC evaluates model using all possible thresholds effectively offsets the influence of changing prevalence.",
    "We show evidence for this claim through a threshold analysis that includes all possible thresholds for all the data samples, models and metrics.",
    "The results show that the more decision thresholds we consider, the most consistent model evaluations we obtain across data of different prevalence.",
    "An implication for researchers and practitioners of model evaluation is that awareness ought to be raised for the underappreciated issue of consistency of model evaluation with respect to prevalence change."
  ]
}